\subsection{biplot}

<<message=TRUE,cache=FALSE>>=
p = describe_data(
  data_GxE, plot_type = "biplot",
  vec_variables = c("y1", "y2", "y3"),
  in_col = "germplasm", labels_on = "germplasm"
  )
@

The name of the list correspond to the pairs of variables displayed.
Note that for each element of the following list, there are as many graph as needed with \texttt{nb\_parameters\_per\_in\_col} parameters per graph.
<<message=TRUE,cache=FALSE>>=
names(p)
p$`y1 - y2`$`-NA|germplasm-1`
@


